  "texts": [
    "Inspired by these works, researchers have begun to explore linearized architectures for computer vision tasks like image [27,103,118], video [48], and 3D [56] understanding.",
    "The rise of linearized LLM has also inspired efficient multimodal models [53,67,70,86,93,115].",
    "However, since images and short clips involve relatively limited sequence lengths, the advantage from linearized architectures is still a controversial problem [103].",
    "In contrast, long video understanding naturally demands models capable of processing extremely long contexts, posing far stricter efficiency requirements.",
    "Recently, AuroraLong [93] combines a ViT with RWKV6 [65] and employs token merging in a projector to compress vision tokens."
  ],
